<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xml:lang="en"
      lang="en"
      metal:use-macro="context/@@main_template/master"
      i18n:domain="rosetta">

<head>
    <title metal:fill-slot="title">Add LP Person</title>
    <!-- Plone style sheet -->
    <style type="text/css" media="screen"> @import url(plone.css);</style>
</head>

<body>

<div metal:fill-slot="main">

    <h1>Please register</h1>

    <div class="documentDescription">
    Main idea here is to show the relevant sections expanded, depending on where
    people came from, and collapse the ones that are less relevant - so they can
    register for Translation and Package Management if they are so inclined.
    </div>

      <form action="join_form" method="post">

        <fieldset>

          <legend>Personal Details</legend>

          <div class="field">
              
              <label>Full Name</label>
  
              <div class="formHelp">
                Enter full name, eg. John Smith.
              </div>
              
              <div></div>
  
                  <input type="text" name="fullname" size="30"
                         tabindex="1" />

          </div>
    
          <div class="field">
            
            <label>User Name</label>

            <span class="fieldRequired" title="Required">(Required)</span>

                    <div class="formHelp">
                    Enter a user name, usually something like
                    'jsmith'. No spaces or special characters. 
                    Usernames and passwords are case sensitive,
                    make sure the caps lock key is not enabled.
                    This is the name used to log in.
                    </div>
            
                <input type="text" name="username" size="30"
                       tabindex="2" />
            </div>

            <div class="field">

                <label>E-mail</label>
    
                <span class="fieldRequired" title="Required">(Required)</span>
    
                      <div class="formHelp">
                        Enter an email address. This is necessary in case the password
                        is lost. We respect your privacy, and will not give the address
                        away to any third parties or expose it anywhere.
                      </div>
    
                      <div></div>
    		  
                    <input type="text" name="email" size="30"
                           tabindex="3" />
            </div>

        </fieldset>

        <fieldset>
            <legend>
                <input type="checkbox" class="noborder" checked="checked" 
                       title="Check this box if you want to be part of the translation of projects" />
            Translation information
            </legend>
        
            <div class="field">
            
                <label>Languages I can translate into</label>
    
                <span class="fieldRequired" title="Required">(Required)</span>
    
                <div class="formHelp">
                Select the languages you are capable of translating into.
                You can always override these on a per-translation basis.
                </div>
                
                <select multiple="multiple">
                    <option>English</option>
                    <option>Spanish</option>
                    <option>French</option>
                    <option>German</option>
                    <option>Norwegian</option>
                    <option>Welsh</option>
                </select>
            </div>

            <div class="field">
            
                <label>Languages I want to use as source languages</label>
    
                <span class="fieldRequired" title="Required">(Required)</span>
    
                <div class="formHelp">
                Select the languages you want to have displayed as reference
                when translating. Typically only one language, but if you're
                translating into Brazilian Portuguese, it might make sense to
                have the Portuguese translation available as a reference.
                </div>
            
                <select multiple="multiple">
                    <option>English</option>
                    <option>Spanish</option>
                    <option>French</option>
                    <option>German</option>
                    <option>Norwegian</option>
                    <option>Welsh</option>
                </select>

                <div class="discreet">
                Note: this should be a specialized widget, we will need a good
                way to select languages everywhere. Maybe the JS-completion
                string/pulldown I've been talking about.
                </div>
            </div>

        </fieldset>

        <fieldset>
            <legend>
                <input type="checkbox" class="noborder" checked="checked" 
                       title="Check this box if you have a project you want to register" />
            Project information
            </legend>
        
            <div class="field">
            
                <label>Project name</label>
    
                <span class="fieldRequired" title="Required">(Required)</span>
    
                <div class="formHelp">
                The "unix name" of the product. All lowercase, and must be 
                uniquely identifiable.
                </div>
            <input type="text" />                
            
            </div>

            <div class="field">
            
                <label>CVS/Subversion/arch repository</label>
    
                <div class="formHelp">
                The details about the upstream repository if you want us to
                track changes.
                </div>
            
                <input type="radio" /> CVS <br />
                <input type="radio" checked="checked" /> Subversion <input type="text" value="Repository address"/> <br />
                <input type="radio" /> arch <br />
                
                                
            </div>

        </fieldset>

    <div class="formControls">

            <input class="context" type="submit"
                   tabindex="5"
                   name="form.button.Register"
                   value="Register" />

            <div class="discreet">
            A password will be generated and 
            e-mailed to you to complete the registration process.
            </div>


        </div>



    </form>
    
</div>

</body>
</html>

